name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: NEW REPORT details how Amazon is failing to provide safe workplaces, stable employment, and adequate pay to its workers in Minnesota, who are disproportionately Black including many East African immigrants.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Proud to be part of the coalition of AGs fighting the unconstitutional Mississippi abortion law at the Supreme Court today. Reproductive rights are human rights. Period.  https://t.co/vtn72FHtHi

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: I believe all protesters, including those protesting Line 3, have a fundamental right to peaceful and lawful protest. Everyone engaged in peaceful protest has a right to expect their First Amendment rights will be respected. 2/2

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: In Minnesota, criminal charging decisions are generally made by county and city attorneys. My office has not brought any charges against Line 3 protesters. Only the county or city attorneys who have brought criminal charges have the power to drop them. 1/2

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Spending my Sunday morning with @MNFarmersUnion fighting against market concentration in agriculture.  It is time for the American people to stick together and restore some fairness for farmers, and all workers, in our great nation.  https://t.co/Z6HYNFkd8s

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Spent my afternoon in Willmar with @greatermncities talking to over 100 city leaders from across MN about opioids and the evening with @PCCmpls discussing how we can come together and advance public safety.  https://t.co/4s5vfPwQle

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: I'm investigating Meta (formerly Facebook) for promoting Instagram to young ppl despite knowing it’s associated with physical & mental health harms. We want info on how Meta increased young users' engagement & if it violated MN consumer-protection law.  https://t.co/lLalzyRAo0

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: I’m grateful to the heroic tenants—who Meldahl bullied, threatened, and belittled for years—who stood up at trial and spoke their truths. My job is to help them & all Minnesotans afford their lives & live with dignity, safety, & respect. This ruling is progress toward that.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: I’m gratified the court also found that the State “has a substantial interest in preventing and deterring such brazen and deplorable illegal business conduct.” This is our first case of using consumer-protection law to protect tenants from fraud and abuse. It’s not the last.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Meldahl has bragged about evicting 99% of his tenants. I sued him in 2019 for violating state consumer-protection laws and preying on low-income tenants in a systematic “eviction for profit” scheme.  https://t.co/0GS92UJhkn

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: The court imposed a significant fine bc it said “landlords are not above the system and consumer protection laws must be followed.” I couldn’t agree more. Court also ruled Meldahl cannot block tenants from calling city inspectors or charge illegally high late-rent fees.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: A court has found that Mpls landlord Steven Meldahl knowingly & in bad faith violated the rights of 267 families he rented to. The court found “credible and compelling” former tenants who testified about housing conditions of “Biblical plague proportions.”  https://t.co/E2FOxhXQUx

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: On this fateful day—3 years since a white supremacist walked into the Tree of Life Synagogue and stole the lives of 11 worshippers in a deadly anti-Semitic attack—I want to ask you to pause and think about the need to stand up firm against hate.   We’re all in this together.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: You bet I did. I will fight this unconstitutional law, and others like it, as long as I can.   https://t.co/gHQKXqL4PH

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: The decision to come out is life-changing. On #NationalComingOutDay, know that whether you have a lot of support or very little, you are loved. As AG and as a fellow human being, I will fight with you & the community for your right to live with dignity, safety, and respect.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Many families have stories about how they came to America—by choice, necessity or force. Indigenous people’s stories are the oldest of all: they were here first and are still here. On #IndigenousPeoplesDay we honor their millennia of stories, strength & sovereignty in this land.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: BREAKING: A federal judge has blocked Texas’s new law that effectively and unconstitutionally blocks access to abortion care for everyone. Proud to have filed an amicus brief in support of the Biden admin’s lawsuit against it. I’m in this fight to the end.  https://t.co/F1eEc6IrRc

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: See this pg for more info. If you think you’re eligible, call my office at (651) 296-3353. We’re here to help anyone who feels they’ve been defrauded for any reason.  https://t.co/bvuUCxmQ6A

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: The AG’s office started investigating in 2013, sued in 2014, then went through 2 trials, appeals & a bankruptcy filing. I’m so proud of staff in my office who dedicated 8 yrs to finally getting justice. That's public service. I hope it helps folks put their lives back together.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Many of these students were ppl of color, low-income, vets or supporting their families while trying to better afford their lives by getting a degree in public service. They paid $40-80K for a degree the schools knew they had no right to offer but aggressively marketed anyway.
